Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:04.24,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As long as people are involved in modern-day crimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.91,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}there are no unsolvable mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.91,0:00:07.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's case is about a mysterious murder weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.61,0:00:09.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Let's use our heads to figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.44,0:00:11.14,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.14,0:00:13.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.25,0:00:15.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:45.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to take a leisurely walk together once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:47.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.26,0:01:52.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so fun about walking with that runt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.63,0:01:54.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.74,0:02:01.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:02.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A little bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.81,0:02:04.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.11,0:02:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It looks okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.01,0:02:08.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.08,0:02:11.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't seem to be hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.42,0:02:16.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew off...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.35,0:02:20.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a weird bird.\NMaybe it had an anemic attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.76,0:02:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from that apartment building!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.04,0:02:34.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.08,0:02:42.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There are only two apartments occupied here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.05,0:02:44.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:47.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We just heard a woman scream from this building!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.85,0:02:52.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure? I didn't hear anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:56.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back. You're back early.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:57.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:00.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, these folks here—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.57,0:03:03.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.07,0:03:05.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's horrible! My husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.30,0:03:08.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was murdered on our balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:12.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you're the one who screamed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.75,0:03:16.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which room is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:18.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Room 715.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:24.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, I looked at the mail board earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:26.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly anybody lives here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.09,0:03:29.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is going to be demolished this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.49,0:03:31.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the only ones living here now
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:35.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,are Imoto-{\i1}san{\i0}, who runs his own business, and Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0} here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:53.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}High heels and two pairs of men's shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:04.82,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(250,0)}Real Estate Agent\NRyusuke Imoto (39)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:08.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been hit in the back of the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:11.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon appears to have been a flower pot or the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:12.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:15.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Dobashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:17.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you kill him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.11,0:04:19.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.02,0:04:31.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the cause of death was brain damage...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.16,0:04:35.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer most likely lifted up a flower pot from behind him
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and brought it down as hard as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.10,0:04:40.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:42.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a mark here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.87,0:04:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe it has something to do with the murder—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:46.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:52.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you ever learn to stop butting in during our investigations?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.71,0:04:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.85,0:04:59.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There definitely is a mark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.58,0:05:04.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems extremely new compared to all the other marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:09.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was Mr. Ryusuke Imoto, 39 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.89,0:05:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and president of NEED, a real estate agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.98,0:05:18.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryusuke's Wife\NTakako Imoto (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:17.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was his wife, Takako-{\i1}san{\i0}, who found him. Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:22.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the person found standing in front of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.87,0:05:24.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0} and the others came rushing in...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.78,0:05:32.54,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Import Company Manager\NTetsuo Dobashi (55)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.91,0:05:29.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Dobashi.\NI manage an import company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:33.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Imoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s former boss and the one who introduced him to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:36.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to see him today about a business matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.42,0:05:38.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His matchmaker, eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:40.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.38,0:05:47.18,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Former Fishing Goods Store Owner\NNorio Terasawa (43)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:45.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa. I live on the 5th floor of this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to run a fishing goods store.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:49.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Used to"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.73,0:05:53.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Imoto took control of my store!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.40,0:05:56.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He used some dirty legal loophole to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.47,0:05:59.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a terrible man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:05.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is he did the same sort of things to these people too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.52,0:06:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:09.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:13.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As their matchmaker, I shouldn't be saying this,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:15.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he and his wife were\Nin the middle of getting divorced
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.83,0:06:18.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there was trouble about the compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.43,0:06:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that wouldn't matter if he died—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she'd get his inheritance instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.53,0:06:23.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.10,0:06:25.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard my husband constantly refused your requests for a loan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.67,0:06:29.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because your company was on the verge of going out of business!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.61,0:06:31.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you couldn't handle it and killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:33.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:36.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Calm down, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:38.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Apartment Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.35,0:06:42.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that main door the only way in and out of this building?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:44.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.69,0:06:48.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only ones who entered besides the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:54.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...were his wife, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}, and Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:58.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, each of you had a decent enough motive to kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.74,0:07:03.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, one of you three murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.91,0:07:05.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.84,0:07:07.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.41,0:07:10.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain the situation when you found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:20.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a little after 5:00 when I arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.06,0:07:22.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, it was just after 5:05.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.76,0:07:26.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I record when everyone enters or leaves the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.43,0:07:29.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be very handy for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:32.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:34.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I came here today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.84,0:07:37.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was to discuss the compensation with my husband one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:40.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just as Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0} mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.08,0:07:43.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He and I have been living apart for quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:45.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:48.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,my husband was practicing\NTai Chi on the balcony by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:50.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tai Chi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:51.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:55.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband did it every morning and evening for his health.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.56,0:07:58.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't notice when I entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:02.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I didn't call out to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.10,0:08:06.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I looked out the balcony again\Nafter using the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:12.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...my husband was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.74,0:08:17.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, your husband died while you were in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:19.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:23.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my asking, but how long were you in the bathroom for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:27.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only about two minutes, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.39,0:08:31.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means your husband died at approximately 5:08.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:33.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While you were in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:37.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,did you hear any sounds or people talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.07,0:08:42.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, when you entered the apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.61,0:08:46.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,were there any shoes by the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.14,0:08:49.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just a pair of my husband's shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.48,0:08:51.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.18,0:08:53.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:57.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Around what time did you first arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:09:00.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A little before 5:00, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:04.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was to meet with Imoto-{\i1}kun{\i0} at 5 o'clock, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.29,0:09:07.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, 4:58.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:10.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as his wife said, the reason I came here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.60,0:09:14.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was to ask for a loan one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.04,0:09:15.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.94,0:09:20.28,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's pointless, no matter how hard you try!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:24.72,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I have no desire or reason to help you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:27.78,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:31.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I went to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:32.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.56,0:09:33.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.56,0:09:37.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stood there for a while, in a daze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.53,0:09:45.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was then that I heard her scream from the other side of the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.20,0:09:50.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I rushed into the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:54.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Imoto-{\i1}san{\i0} was dead on the balcony, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.75,0:09:59.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.55,0:10:03.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I have to do with it?\NI wasn't in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.82,0:10:05.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We just need to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.49,0:10:08.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Around what time did you leave the building?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:12.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was a little before 5:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.56,0:10:14.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,4:50, to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:19.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he didn't return until just after 5:12.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.07,0:10:20.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:21.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"But"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.07,0:10:27.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He came back from his golf practice rather earlier than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:30.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I changed my mind on the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.18,0:10:32.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been a bit spur-of-the-moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:49.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't in the building when Imoto-{\i1}san{\i0} was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so you're not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.57,0:10:56.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The issue here is with his wife and Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:10:57.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First you, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you found your husband's body\Nafter you left the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.48,0:11:05.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's the possibility that you never went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.48,0:11:09.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that you killed your husband,\Npretended to find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.42,0:11:10.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then screamed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:12.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:13.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:17.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you went up to the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.39,0:11:19.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after Imoto-{\i1}san{\i0} refused to lend you money,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.26,0:11:22.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's a possibility\Nyou were actually in his office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or with him on the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.44,0:11:29.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All you can see from here\Nis a small part of the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:33.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also possible that when his wife came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you were on the balcony or in his office,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:38.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,killed the victim while she was in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then went up to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:41.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.65,0:11:45.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was already on the roof\Nby the time she came in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.86,0:11:49.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She even said that only Imoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s shoes were by the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.59,0:11:53.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also possible that she didn't remember correctly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.26,0:11:57.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you have proof that you were on the roof the whole time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.63,0:11:59.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.47,0:12:02.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there was no one on the roof, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I heard a sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:07.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.31,0:12:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was a loud, metallic sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:12.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from the area around this balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.25,0:12:14.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard a sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.45,0:12:17.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A metallic one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:21.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, could that sound have been something hitting the handrail?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.86,0:12:27.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, there's a fresh mark on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:32.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears something hit it from below...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.00,0:12:36.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! That's the sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.24,0:12:40.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The marks look similar...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.41,0:12:44.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the other mark was made coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:45.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.62,0:12:49.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no question that someone hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.32,0:12:52.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear the sound, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:53.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.62,0:12:57.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I probably didn't hear it because I was in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.56,0:12:59.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:03.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why would someone put a mark\Nin a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.53,0:13:05.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.40,0:13:07.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This handrail seems suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:12.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but in my opinion none of them\Nseem to be lying, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.01,0:13:13.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.21,0:13:15.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because Dobashi heard a sound from the handrail
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that isn't proof that he was on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.45,0:13:19.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He or the victim might've made the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:23.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while he was on the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:27.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if the killer was someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that means they flew in like a bird to kill the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.29,0:13:33.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then flew off the exact same way they came!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:36.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would never, ever happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.07,0:13:38.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You do have a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:43.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A bird? A bird?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.21,0:13:48.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it, the spot where the bird fell—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:51.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}-was over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:54.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Directly in front of the mark on this handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.65,0:13:56.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The location where the victim collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:58.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The location where the bird fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:00.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The mark on the handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.33,0:14:06.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}An abandoned building across the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:08.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.00,0:14:09.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:12.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The murder weapon wasn't a flower pot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.80,0:14:16.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(0,250)}The killer was that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:24.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My deductions can't possibly be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:27.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She's his wife, who lives separately from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.33,0:14:29.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's the president of an import company.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:33.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And he's the former owner of a fishing goods store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:35.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:37.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:40.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be returning to my apartment now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.61,0:14:42.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.32,0:14:43.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.45,0:14:45.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can't let that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.52,0:14:48.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I have to make the old man realize it somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:14:56.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:06.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you figured anything out, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:10.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:13.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you may leave, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:14.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.91,0:15:16.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.78,0:15:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.55,0:15:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.79,0:15:28.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.51,0:15:43.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come on, realize it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:48.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.08,0:15:51.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the spot where the victim collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:57.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the mark on the handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:16:00.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.13,0:16:04.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, that bird fell down there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:13.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.04,0:16:16.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim, the mark, that bird, and that abandoned building!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.88,0:16:19.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all directly lined up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:22.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who did it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.02,0:16:25.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.32,0:16:27.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too ahead of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.25,0:16:31.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain everything atop that abandoned building!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.79,0:16:33.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.14,0:16:49.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:53.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you checking for in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:56.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see what this has to do with the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.82,0:17:03.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone gather around here, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.56,0:17:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, allow me to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:11.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, Dobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:14.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have any of you ever been here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.67,0:17:16.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.70,0:17:18.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.74,0:17:21.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor have I.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.57,0:17:24.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.01,0:17:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the victim's balcony from here, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:32.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but what does that have to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:35.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever heard of surf casting, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.25,0:17:36.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Surf casting?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.59,0:17:41.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a type of fishing that uses a so-called "spinning reel"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.73,0:17:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to allow the fisher to cast the line\Nsome dozens of meters out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.53,0:17:47.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used this technique from here
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:53.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to hit the victim's head with a weight as he stood on the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.07,0:17:53.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.74,0:17:56.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.08,0:18:02.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This footprint is the proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:05.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The left foot is in front and with a lot of weight on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.95,0:18:11.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was made when the killer flung the pole in an overhand fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:13.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:19.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was killed,\Nthe victim was performing Tai Chi,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:22.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which is known for its slow movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.44,0:18:24.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.07,0:18:28.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer swung the fishing pole\Nwhen he turned away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.01,0:18:38.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And as it was reeled in—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.72,0:18:41.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,—the weight hit the handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:44.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's the sound I heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.29,0:18:50.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer didn't realize the weight had left a mark when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.66,0:18:55.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there was one other miscalculation on the killer's part.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.60,0:19:00.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As the weight was being reeled in,\Nit hit a bird in mid-air.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.74,0:19:08.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The bird you picked up had probably received a concussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:13.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}, it's over 30 meters to that balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.12,0:19:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could someone really cast a weight that far with such precision?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:19.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With enough practice, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.73,0:19:23.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially for someone who's good at surf casting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:27.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.87,0:19:29.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.74,0:19:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those shoes you're wearing right now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.37,0:19:36.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,should undoubtedly match these footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.04,0:19:39.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we look hard enough around this abandoned building,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.71,0:19:40.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll probably—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:44.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! There's something on the ground here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:48.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.29,0:19:50.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what this is! It's a pole grip!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.59,0:19:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A pole grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.89,0:19:52.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:56.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes after fishermen connect fishing rods together,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:19:58.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they won't come undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.43,0:20:00.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So to prevent their hands from slipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:05.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they place rubber tubes or rubber bands\Nnear where the rods connect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.34,0:20:08.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then pull the rods apart while twisting them in opposite directions!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.34,0:20:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty smart to know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:14.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to see it on a TV fishing show yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.28,0:20:17.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, they had their gloves off when they used these.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.42,0:20:18.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they would slip!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.88,0:20:23.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer's fingerprints should be on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.12,0:20:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Terasawa-{\i1}san{\i0}. Your fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:34.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help but laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:36.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He took over my store
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:40.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and said he was going to build a fashion building in its place!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.41,0:20:46.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'd give up ownership if he'd just spare the store, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.78,0:20:50.62,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no point in keeping this dinky store around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:53.82,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's so fun about catching fish, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:55.19,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.19,0:20:58.25,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What do you losers see in it at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.67,0:21:13.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My precious fishing rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:17.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He destroyed it before my very eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.81,0:21:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I absolutely couldn't let him get away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.03,0:23:06.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your detective work last night was amazing, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.33,0:23:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My opinion of you keeps getting better!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.30,0:23:15.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cases like that are a piece of cake for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.48,0:23:19.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Did he actually make that fishing rod toy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.15,0:23:22.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}to make me realize it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got something!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:26.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Got you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.06,0:23:34.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.33,0:23:35.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.13,0:23:41.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who am I kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.17,0:23:48.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back here, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.98,0:23:54.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This guy's one of the men in black!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.65,0:23:56.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I finally found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.39,0:24:01.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go before the bomber gets away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.86,0:24:04.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah! So that's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:08.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In the eyes of the killer,\Nthis was an unexpected murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.61,0:24:14.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.62,0:24:19.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Cloakroom Tag
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.62,0:24:21.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, the men in black suits will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.67,0:24:23.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, I'm gonna go back to being an adult too.
